ical fiction has always posed: what can fiction do with history that history cannot?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictiony21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHistory in literature. 0aMemory in literature. 0aWar in literature. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aPostmemory.  acontemporary fiction.  ahistorical fiction.  ahistoriographic metafiction.  amemory.  aqueer fiction.  aworld wars.1 aAlden, Natasha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610260740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526102607423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526102607/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles